social_posts.post_text:
In September of 2021, I shared my experience about self love. How i overcame comparing my self with others and instead focused on growing into the person I am today, someone who I am proud to be.

This photo is from March of 2023. During this time, I fell back into my old ways. I stopped taking care of myself, i compared myself with girls on the internet, trying to change myself to “be like them” and lost all confidence within myself. As we all know, we go through multiple life experiences that shapes up into our selves today. Everyone is different and has a story to tell. I knew if I wanted to get back to who I was, I had to let go of everything that was distracting me and wasn’t putting any good into my life. Would I say it was easy, absolutely not. Social media plays a huge role and easily allows for anyone to compare themselves/lower their confidence for not looking like those on the internet. It becomes a toxic place that is not good for your mental health. 

There is a phrase that I like to say, people think it’s quirky, however I believe it describes when the next chapter of your life arrives, you’re ready for the changes there is to come. 

It is only the beginning <3
